oc:kn_12dc9437 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When executing any launch campaign" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never rely on a single launch event or a single channel. Don't treat rented or borrowed channels as your only strategy—always funnel attention into owned channels." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Single-event launches create short-lived spikes. Rented channels give speed but not stability. Sustainable growth requires compounding owned audience relationships." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_2dba1ce8 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When planning any launch channel strategy" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Structure all launch marketing across three channel types using the ORB Framework: Owned (email, blog, community), Rented (social media, app stores), Borrowed (guest content, partnerships, influencers). Everything should ultimately lead back to owned channels." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Owned channels compound in value over time and are immune to algorithm changes, while rented and borrowed channels provide speed but not stability." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_4df2d0ef a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:RecoveryTactic ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When a launch fails to meet expectations" ;
    oc:directiveContent "If a launch underperforms: diagnose failure causes (insufficient audience, wrong channels, weak messaging), analyze which channels produced whatever signups you got and double down, iterate on messaging, leverage early users for testimonials, and try new distribution channels." ;
    oc:hasRationale "A failed launch is recoverable if you diagnose root causes and act on the signals you do have rather than abandoning the effort entirely." .

oc:kn_a0829aea a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:WorkflowStrategy ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When planning a new product launch from scratch" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Launch using five progressive phases: Internal Launch → Alpha Launch → Beta Launch → Early Access Launch → Full Launch. Each phase has distinct goals and actions that build on the previous one." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Launching is not a one-day event but a phased process that builds momentum. Skipping phases risks launching to an unprepared audience with an unvalidated product." .

oc:kn_b91780ee a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:PreFlightCheck ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Before starting any launch strategy task" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Check for product marketing context file (.agents/product-marketing-context.md or .claude/product-marketing-context.md) before asking the user questions. Use existing context and only ask for gaps." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Avoids redundant questions and ensures recommendations are grounded in the user's actual product positioning and audience." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_c4da2d08 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When deciding how to announce ongoing product updates post-launch" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Classify updates as Major (new features/overhauls → full multi-channel campaign), Medium (integrations/UI enhancements → targeted announcement), or Minor (bug fixes/tweaks → changelog only). Stagger announcements rather than shipping everything at once." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Not every update deserves the same level of fanfare. Proper calibration prevents announcement fatigue while signaling active development." .

oc:kn_ee146d36 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Standard ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When planning a Product Hunt launch" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Product Hunt requires significant pre-launch preparation: build relationships with influential supporters weeks in advance, optimize listing assets, study successful launches, and prepare for all-day engagement on launch day. Convert PH traffic into owned relationships (email signups) post-launch." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Product Hunt is competitive and produces short-lived traffic spikes. Success depends on preparation and follow-through, not just showing up." .

